                Definition:

                
                    The force exerted per unit of area by the atmosphere as a consequence
of gravitational attraction upon the "column" of air lying directly above
the point in question. 
                
                

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            Glossary of Weather and Climate, American Meteorological Society, 1996.  
                        
                    
                    

                    

                
            


       







    
    
    
        
    

    
